orbitSensitivity.title: Orbit Sensitivity
orbitSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves around the orbit. Higher is faster

distanceSensitivity.title: Distance Sensitivity
distanceSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves in and out. Higher is faster

distanceMax.title: Distance Max
distanceMax.description: Setting this at 0 will give an infinite distance limit

inertiaFactor.title: Inertia Factor
inertiaFactor.description: Higher value means that the camera will continue moving after the user has stopped dragging. 0 is fully responsive.

focusEntity.title: Focus Entity
focusEntity.description: Entity for the camera to focus on. If blank, then the camera will use the whole scene

frameOnStart.title: Frame on Start
frameOnStart.description: Frames the entity or scene at the start of the application."

orbitSensitivity.title: Orbit Sensitivity
orbitSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves around the orbit. Higher is faster

distanceSensitivity.title: Distance Sensitivity
distanceSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves in and out. Higher is faster

numFrames.description: Number of frames to play before looping

schema.name: name
schema.description: Name for the font face for the canvas font to reference

schema.name: assetName
schema.description: If possible, keep this unique to make this easy to find in the assets registry!

schema.name: fontFaces
schema.description: This has to be written as though it was in a CSS file (https://www.w3schools.com/cssref/pr_font_font-family.asp)

schema.name: textureSize
schema.description: The larger the size, the more VRAM is used. More textures are created to fit the glyphs as the canvas font is updated

schema.name: fontSize
schema.description: The larger the size, the sharper the glyph but the more space it takes up on the texture

bodyBackgroundColor.title: Body Background Color
bodyBackgroundColor.description: Background color of body element (where the banner should be displayed). Make sure the checkbox above is checked!

debugConfig.title: Debug / Testing Mode
debugConfig.description: Force safe areas to be applied to the UI. Useful testing layouts without a device.

resizeOnInput.title: Resize when input received
resizeOnInput.description: Resize the canvas every time when an input event received? May cause slight CPU overhead in some games
